14:30〜17:00まで提供しています❣️
「本日のアフタヌーンティー」とダージリンティーです😋
前回の時は、3段目のスコーンが2個あったのに、1個しか無く😱しかも小さくなってるし😂と思いながら😋あっという間に、2・3段目を完食しちゃいました😁
勿論😍おかわり可能なので、サンドイッチとスコーン2個&大好きなクロテッドクリームを追加😋更にスコーン1個&クロテッドクリームのおかわりをいただいちゃいました👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻寝不足で辛かったけど、頑張って食べました😉
(2019年7月11日)

text:
7-13 July 2019. I was honored to be one of 32 delegates for Hitachi Young Leaders Initiative (HYLI) 2019, Hitachi’s flagship youth program that brings together outstanding students from eight Asian countries –Indonesia, Japan, Malaysia, Myanmar, Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam, and Japan – to discuss the theme of 'Digital Transformation for a Sustainable Future', where we learn how technology can be used to better society within four main themes: Youth Opportunity, Living Environment, Mobility and Well-being for its 15th edition since the first inception in 1996.

Huge appreciation for Hitachi Asia Ltd and Global Initiatives (especially Melissa Wong and Christian Bustamante) plus everyone who had been involved during the whole duration of the project. 
Thank you for the fruitful and joyful moments that I had during the program!

#throwback #HYLI2019

Here's a big thank you to everyone who attended the show, and to the  vendors who spent the day with us. The theme of the showcase @interconsin was beautifully conceptualised by @blancstudios.co and set up by @singseesoon. We hope all of you managed to get really nice pics that day! More photos and details about the showcase are up on our site. The link is on our bio today!

12.07.2019 - HYLI (Highly) 2019 🇸🇬 Hitachi: “Inspire The Next!” 🌟💫👍🏻 A post now to end off my HYLI 2019 experience on a positive note! 😇🤗 Apart from my personal Black-Gold theme; I have other themes such as MBS theme, Mercedes Theme, Infinity Theme, 《狮魂 Lion Spirit, Lion Valour, Lion Roar Theme》etc.

So, do you know what’s the hidden message behind this beautiful poster featuring MBS, Changi Airport, GBTB, etc?

Well, it’s this! 
I shall quote Ambassador Ong Keng Yong verbatim here: “It features the concept of Urbanisation”. One main takeaway from Ambassador Ong’s speech is the acronym and importance of: 《TEE-UP》! Yes, I have not forgotten those important messages and insights that he has shared on Friday. 😎

Nonetheless, my special thanks to Hitachi for having me at this interesting forum. 😇

THANKS also to the wonderful human who invited me for this meaningful event as a guest! 
Really much appreciated! 🙏🏻👍🏻🙆🏼‍♂️🤝🥂 It has been my honour and pleasure to have the opportunity to join everyone at HYLI 2019! 
Congratulations on your making HYLI 2019 a success! Definitely not easy to organise this high-scale forum too! 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻 It could be my first & last encounter with HYLI. It might also not be my final brush with HYLI. Nobody knows! Because I don’t know too! 🤷🏻‍♂️ I built to last! I still remember to slow down and smell the roses 🌹 
So, I still wish to say: “Overall, it feels really great to be present at HYLI 2019!!! Cheers!!!” 🥂💫😇🌈👍🏻🌟 #hyli2019

text:
12.07.2019 - HYLI 2019

Had a photo with some youth delegates. They are either very interesting or friendly. 
It’s been wonderful meeting them! Cheers!! 🌟🥂🌈😊 The first one from 🇮🇩 spoke to me on Day 01 and we hit off well since Day 01!

He told me: “I like your energy!” on Day 01 & I thanked him kindly.

So, after witnessing his presentation on stage~ I decided to reciprocate him with the exact same words, “I like your energy too!” on Day 04 (my Day 02) 😂👍🏻 Hahahas! (Slide 2) is a short moment of his presentation. (Slide 3) is also a friendly delegate from the land of the rising sun, aka 🇯🇵. She does satellite research which is kinda interesting. Now, I understand the rationale behind her choice of “Space” for her IG. 🙏🏻😂 (Slide 4) is yet another youth delegate representing 🇸🇬. Nice! 👏🏻😊

We often hear people say game changing year. Every year is game changing year when it comes to Axe Factor. Barely 1 year old and we won the National Business Award 2019! We were among the Giants of the industry. There are listed companies like Singtel and yet, we were judged and chosen to win this award among many others due to the uniqueness of our venture.

We pioneered a new sport in Singapore. We broke impossibles after impossibles throughout our young journey, and we will continue to do so for years to come.

Axe throwing is more than just a novelty. It's a Sport. One with the potential to go international and have it's own ecosystem of Sports men and women. Big things are coming. Mark my words.

And if you haven't tried axe throwing yet (not because I want your business), what are you waiting for? Hit me up and let's hurl some axes! #ButIDoWantYourBusinessLa #SBRAWARDS #Axefactorsg #TheMostBadassThingYouCanDoToday

初海外でございます
(初飛行機でした億男とコーヒーが冷めないうちにを見ました←めちゃくちゃいい。泣いた)
成田→シンガポール航空→MRT→ホテル→チャイナタウン駅→ショッピングモールやら野外の屋台やら→チャイナコンプレックス(雰囲気いいていうかこええ)→お土産やさん→野外のわりときれいめな中華でバクテー、小籠包、ワンタン麺的なん、ライムジュース→旦那さん激体調不良→なんとか回復→ホテル戻る→セブンイレブン なんでか店員さんにちょっとおこられる

中華料理屋で「モシッソヨ」と声をかけられ「のー‼️あいむじゃぱにーず‼️モシッソヨ→こーりあん、あいむ、じゃぱにーず、おいしい❗️」て楽しかった

text:
From the moment you arrive, we will be discreetly managing and personally overseeing every detail of your weekend ensuring you have a stress free and memorable experience. Our suggested hotel is in the historic Kampong Glam neighbourhood, famous for its Malay heritage and traditional shophouses. One of the oldest urban districts of Singapore the area has an eclectic blend of history, culture and a super-trendy lifestyle scene.
Inclusions:
• Personally welcomed on your arrival
• Chauffeured airport transfers to and from your hotel
• A short ride on the convenient and efficient metro service gets you to, and from
the circuit in no time. Alternatively its just a 15 minute walk directly to the circuit
• Personally escorted to your race hospitality/viewing
• 4 x nights accommodation in a double room in our 4* hotel situated steps from
Kampong Glam district. The hotel has a number of restaurants and bars, a business centre, gym, pool and spa. It is just a few minutes walk to the MRT station and just 15 minutes walk to the circuit
• Accommodation includes breakfast
• Hosted and discreetly managed throughout by our onsite team
• Restaurant bookings, club access, private excursions etc can all be arranged
on your behalf 
Info@Luxperience travelgroup.com

How often do you change jobs? 🤷🏻‍♂️ I was in the same ballroom with many many people who stayed in the same job for at least 20 years and above! 😵 One even stayed for 45 years! 😳 win liao lor 👍🏽
.
Back at @aiasingapore again to host their Agency Long Service Awards ceremony, recognizing close to 200 individuals for their commitment, dedication and passion in the same job. 👏🏼 Congratulations to all winners!
.
Reading hundreds of names while pacing the entire ceremony aren’t easy but always full of fun and laughter when working with the team at AIA! Thank You for having me again! ☺️
.

.

[VIA: @straits_times: Singaporean Spurs fans welcoming the players as soon as arrived at Singapore on Thursday]

Thursday, July 18th around 8am SG, the fans welcoming the Tottenham players on Mandarin Oriental Hotel, Raffles Ave., Downtown Singapore. As soon as the players get off from the bus, the fans directly meet them and ask for the autograph. Most of the fans were been waiting since early morning today.
-
Some of the fans were confessed that even they had work or classes today, they're willing to wait and meet the players.
-

清掃は一日2回入ります。午前中に普通に清掃して、夕方はオープンベットに作り変えて、足元にマットとか敷いてくれて、チョコとドリンク追加されてて❤️
現地のお菓子と紅茶も置いてくれちゃったりしてー😊
ロイヤルハワイアンだって、アウトリガーホテルだってここまでサービス無かったよー😍

text:
﻿
【リッツカールトン  究極のホスピタリティが教えてくれる事。】﻿
﻿
プールサイドで娘とふたり﻿写真の撮りあいっこをしていたら ﻿
﻿
﻿
スタッフが駆けつけて﻿
「ここのアングルから撮るのが映えるよ！」﻿
﻿
﻿
みたいなことを言いながら﻿
娘と一緒に何枚も写真を撮ってくれた。﻿
﻿
﻿
その後、ビーチベッドに横たわっていたら﻿
「こっちの方が眺望が良いよ」と言って﻿場所のチェンジを手伝ってくれた。﻿
﻿
﻿
しばらくすると暑いからと﻿
飲み物を持ってきてくれ﻿
ベッドごと日陰に移動してくれた。﻿
﻿
﻿
なんとも至れり尽くせり。﻿
﻿
﻿
起業したての頃 ある先輩が﻿
リッツのホスピタリティについて﻿
学ぶといいよと教えてくれた。﻿
﻿
﻿
プロフェッショナルなら﻿
専門的な知識や技術があるのは当たり前。﻿
﻿
﻿
でも、それだけじゃダメ。﻿
﻿
﻿
お客さまの視点で 、﻿
お客さまが何を求めているのか？﻿
常に心を配ること。﻿
﻿
﻿
ビジネスをするうえで最も大切な事を﻿リッツのホスピタリティが教えてくれる。﻿
﻿
﻿
＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝﻿
﻿
▼フォローミー▼﻿﻿
@shion_nishijima ﻿﻿

経験・知識ゼロ起業初心者にもできる ﻿﻿
﻿﻿
﻿﻿
「最新時短 SNS集客法！」 ﻿﻿
﻿﻿
★--プレゼント受け取り方法--★﻿﻿
shionとLineでお友達になってね！﻿﻿
﻿﻿
①LineのID検索で＠amj4198aを検索﻿﻿
（＠マークをお忘れなく）﻿﻿
﻿﻿
②トップページの自己紹介にあるURLを﻿タップして、Line@でお友達になる。 ﻿﻿
↓↓↓﻿﻿

---
Slept in over at girlfriend's house, woke up to a birthday song surprise from @charlottelum with my favourite birthday cake.

Next she booked a staycay! Off to @ritzcarltonmilleniasingapore
we go! Simply the sweetest to plan all the surprises and made sure everything is something that I would like for sure.

To many more years of birthday songs and weird photos. Thank you for accepting my weirdness and being weird with me. ♥

text:
Tile painting for INClusive Awards & Appreciation Nite 2019.

Participants were taught on painting techniques.
Stroke works, layering technique and dry brush effects.

All are doing it for the first time, some were shy at first but willing to try after seeing the completed artwork of their friend’s. 👍

They also learnt how to ‘save’ their artwork by enhancing it with simple outline n dots.

One fulfilling part is to see people being amazed by themselves and their artwork, when they thought that they can’t ‘do Art’. Plus, no matter what the outcome is, it’s Art after all 😊

text:
“In the jungle, the mighty jungle
The lion sleeps tonight
In the jungle the quiet jungle
The lion sleeps tonight.” (The Lion Sleeps Tonight, song by The Tokens)

This Lion City awakes to the rumble of onrushing leopards, buffalo, bears, cats, all manner of tracks & wheels - the mobile entourage of a mighty fighting force. Week after week since early May, the mobile column team go through their paces to keep their vehicles well tuned and to move together in well drilled synchronised fashion. So many moving parts, literally. To keep the pattern together and running smoothly in connection with the entire parade is no mean feat. Give the guys a smile and/or a simple wave or a thumbs up as they drive by, it will encourage them greatly. 👍👍 #SAFArmour50 #SingaporeArmedForces #OneSAF #NDP2019 #NDP19 #OurSingapore #NDP2019MobileColumn #NDP19NEShow1 #SingaporeArmy #SAFArmour #SwiftandDecisive #OnceArmourAlwaysArmour #TheForceTheFamilyTheFuture #ArmourMafiaFamily #MilitaryEnthusiast #MilitaryGeek #Saturday #Singapore #Saturday #FairmontSingapore #SwissotelTheStamford #Nikon #NikonD500 #PlanesPatchesPeople

text:
In 1999, MAC sponsored the world premiere and tour of Stella Kon's Emily of Emerald Hill, directed by the late great Krishen Jit. This would be MAC’s very first foray into collaborating with theatre artists and companies in Asia.

This co-production between Dramalab KL and Wild Rice opened in Kuala Lumpur and toured to Hong Kong Fringe, before Wild Rice's debut in Singapore at the Jubilee Hall, Raffles Hotel in April 2000.

For two decades now, MAC has been providing its high performance makeup, teaching, designing and executing makeup looks for all WILD RICE productions worldwide.

Our long term partnership is cemented and bouyed by our shared values: Artistry, Individuality, Community, Trendsetting and Social Responsibility.

Today, MAC's visionary and generous support of theatre extends to many other theatre and arts companies in Singapore. We look forward to more amazing adventures at Wild Rice @ Funan.

On behalf of all our artists and audiences, we thank you and salute you MAC. 🌈✨❤️🙏❤️✨🌈 p.s. Emily wears "Russian Red"

#blazethetrail #attitudeofgratitude #sgtheatre #WRFunan #MACCosmetics #sharedvalues #workwiththebest

text: Inside the famous Chijmes Cathedral is the iconic chapel. Constructed in the neo-classical gothic style, the restored building is replete with terrazzo tiled floors, twining stairs, delicate stained glass panels and elegant Corinthian columns. The Anglo-French architecture reflects the influence of the European colonialists in early Singapore’s art and architecture.

text:
Dulu pas masih kuliah semester akhir pertanyaan mainstreamnya begini:
‘Mbak Onik kapan skripsi?’ ‘Mbak Onik sudah lulus?’ ‘Mbak Onik kapan sidang?’ Terus sudah lulus ada pertanyaan lagi:
‘Sudah kerja?’ ‘Kerja dimana?’ ‘Belum dapat kerja sampe skg? Lulus kapan Emang?’ Udah dapet kerja masih nggak tau diri juga tanya:
‘Nikahnya kapan?’ ‘Udah punya pacar?’ ‘Kapan nikah sama yang di foto berdua itu?’ Well well, pertanyaan-pertanyaan itu juga akan terus ada seiring perjalanan kita hidup di dunia. Gak bakalan ada pertanyaan dari manusia kalo kita nanti mati kan?. Bahkan mati pun nanti akan diminta pertanggungjawaban juga. 
Kadang ada orang yang nggak sadar bahwa pertanyaan-pertanyaan tersebut tidak pernah ditanyakan ke dia sendiri. Cukup satu pertanyaan saja. ‘Apakah diriku bahagia?’ Tentunya berlaku untuk diri sendiri. Kalo tidak mau diberikan pertanyaan-pertanyaan itu lebih baik tidak usah bertanya. Diam itu emas? Gak hanya emas tapi perak perunggu duwit deposito saham apartemen rumah tanah 💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾💃🏾 Btw kata-kata cem novel ini inspired by @ajengkarr ❤️ Oiya, selayang pandang yang pernah nonton Film Crazy Rich Asians pasti familier sama tempat ini 😎😎😎 #happy #holiday

blurb: Marina Square Shopping Mall
text:
«В 1861 году ездила в Турцию, а сейчас уже 2348, но вот вам моя фотка с подписью «как классно было отдыхать», чтобы вы не забыли что я куда-то ездила, а то я ж сижу дома последние 500 лет, а выпендриваться надо».
⠀ 
Именно так в моем понимании выглядели все эти товарищи, которые выкладывают чуть ли не год фотки из путешествия. А сейчас я приехала сама и такая «Ну куча же классных фоток, хочется выложить!». Короче, я всех этих людей поняла... Но все равно это бесит, надо срочно выкладывать все одной большой галереей, иначе реально постить можно ещё год. Хотя, почему нет? Но жизнь то идёт, у меня 20 июля День Рождения и вообще дальше в Уфе я сидеть не намерена, это-то всё тоже надо выкладывать 😨
⠀ 
Я не знаю, помогите разобраться! Выкладывать фотки через полгода после поездки это стрем или норм? Я сама никак не решу 🧐

text:
In a terrible abuse of power and insider information manipulation, I'm putting down here part of what I wrote in their yearbook. (I will pay for this, however, in the very last photograph of this album, which Julian made me take.)
Congratulations, MPM Class of 2018/19 for having come all this way on your journey of singular milestones. On this arc, you have walked alongside footprints of many who have made this journey before you. But yours alone will form the boundary-defining moments for the Lee Kuan Yew School's Master of Public Management.
Your journey now goes forwards along different trajectories. We want to continue to be with you on those arcs, celebrating with you your triumphs, just as we stand alongside you on challenges you face.
So, this is not goodbye. Come back to visit us, continue to tell us your stories.

name: Singapore Indoor Stadium
text:
In the movie 'Intimate Strangers/완벽한 타인', there's a famous line that goes "A person has at least three lives. A public one, a private one, and a secret one". Mina's injury and dropout from Twicelights Tour kind of shows this couldn't be more true. In her public life as an idol, she is hugely successful - she is in one of the most successful K-pop girl groups of all time, and has achieved great commercial success in both South Korea and Japan, and in fact globally. But it's heartbreaking to see that her private life is totally segregated from the public one. Behind the scenes in her private life she suffers from knee injury and subsequently mental anxiety, while she still performed highly professionally in her public life by giving performances despite the injury. In terms of her secret life, who knows. Maybe she is having other difficulties, maybe she has other ambitions outside idol-ship, or maybe she doesn't. The sasaengs/사생 probably usually aims at idols' secret life but few of them even get to the bottom of the private one. While from a ONCE's perspective, my biggest wish is that the gap between Mina's public and private lives could be narrowed, which means she could worry a little less when off the stage, and can enjoy her public life fully.
#twice #twicelights #mina

text:
感言時間每一位成員都提到他們一定會已9人狀態再回來的，有困難大家都要一起面對，也要大家注意身體健康
多賢講感言講到哭 SANA過去抱抱她真的超暖的（SAIDA❤️)
彩瑛提到MINA的時候我又哭了（是迷彩呀😭）
喜歡看她們成員之間的互動，看到大家互相鼓勵互相安慰真的很感動😢
聽到子瑜全程用中文覺得好親切，第一次親耳聽到他說中文竟然不是在台灣
娜璉用英文講感言真的嚇到大家了，看來真的為了美國做很多準備，但後來又切回韓語模式😂 還有恭喜娜璉的腹肌終於出現了🤣
MOMO竟然說新加坡最棒的東西 第一是辣椒蟹而不是ONCE 然後馬上更正😂緩和一下大家的情緒
怎麼可以這麼可愛🥰
一直到演唱會結束大家的心都還是有點沈重
但沒有人會責怪她們
只希望她們有時間可以好好休息
下次九人完整體一定會看的🤙🏻
期待看到健健康康的九位成員❤️
第二篇不知道發生什麼事
我又重發了😅
#twice #once #twicelights
#twicelightsinsg #najeongmosajimidachaetzu 
#getwellsoonmina 
#nineornone

name: Singapore Indoor Stadium
text:
Day 2 concert 
第一次為了看演唱會飛到國外
是因為要見我最愛的TWICE 
好不容易努力爭取到這次機會
卻在出發前一天收到令人難過的消息：「MINA因身體狀況將不再參加接下來的世界巡迴演唱會」
給了我一個大打擊  因為我每個成員都非常喜歡
也非常非常愛MINA  這種狀況竟然發生在她們身上讓我非常心疼
一方面擔心她的身體狀況，也擔心自己沒有心情好好享受演唱會
還好演唱會開場時氣氛都非常好  大家的心情看起來也還不錯
大家真的都美到無話可說🤤
但到了演唱會過1/3
大部分粉絲在AFTER MOON時把手燈換上MINA的應援色mint 
還有YOU IN MY HEART 把手燈關掉開啟手機的手電筒應援
竟然把子瑜還有志效弄哭了
覺得好心痛 大家心情肯定都不好受的
中間的小分隊舞台真的超棒的
SANA 多賢 子瑜的dance for you 真的美到說不出話
好喜歡MOMO志效的雙人舞台😍超精彩
娜璉 定延 彩瑛的舞台雖然4缺1 但還是好棒😭
在演唱會尾聲時，播放了新加坡粉絲準備的影片，影片中剛好出現MINA在之前說過“It wasn’t an easy decision, but being a singer was my dream, so I have to try really hard while I can.” 我從這段開始一直哭到成員們講完感言
影片結束時 畫面上的成員都哭了 
台上台下瞬間哭成一片
畢竟這是她們第一場少了MINA的演唱會
突然要面對這麼大的轉變，也沒有時間讓他們準備好面對接下來的難關
#twice #once #twicelights 
#twicelightsinsg 
#nayeon #jeongyeon #momo #sana #jihyo #mina 
#dahyun #chaeyoung #tzuyu 
#weloveyoumina #getwellsoonmina

text:
“Look at all your friends and peers doing better than you. What’s your excuse? Do better”.
-
The years spent as a youth and growing up to be an adult can be some of the most worrying, even depressing, times for certain people. You see your friends get married while you remain single and unwanted. You witness old school peers climb up the social ladder while you deal with your own loneliness - at home and at work. Families and friends sometimes try to reach out to you but their words are neither comforting nor supportive. You dont know who to trust and you feel overwhelmed because you feel so rushed to accomplish 1001 things before you reach a certain age.
-
As bad as things seem, there is always a solution to our problems. Rasulullah (peace be upon him) was once a youth too, going through some of the same struggles that we face. We see in him what can possibly be the best advice for the young people of this generation.
-
Let’s find out how our Prophet lived out his youthful years during this year’s summit. Tickets 🎫 are available now via www.spiritualsummit.sg | ⭐⭐⭐ Save more when you get our FULL ACCESS PASS for admission to all 5 Conferences! 🌟🌟🌟 Get special discounts when you sign-up in a large group!
-

Conference 1: His Youth
Saturday, 20th July
2.00PM-5.00PM
Suntec International Convention Centre
Hall 406
(In conjunction with Plaza Agora)
-
Email us at info@safinah.sg to learn more. See you there! #spiritualsummit

address_json: {"street_address": "1 Raffles Boulevard Suntec City", "zip_code": "039593", "city_name": "Singapore", "region_name": "", "country_code": "SG", "exact_city_match": false, "exact_region_match": false, "exact_country_match": false}
text:
What a dynamic showcase of organic special quality and unique food concepts and specialty foods at the @speciality_asia @rpb_asia joint trade show @suntecsingapore where we witnessed various trade partners coming from Romania, Poland, Taiwan amongst many other countries to offer a whole array of unique concepts and bespoke fine food curations. Organised by Montgomery Asia, Speciality & Fine Food Asia (SFFA) and Restaurant Pub & Bar Asia (RPB Asia) are dedicated trade platforms that connect gourmet food & drink producers and purveyors with decision makers in the retail, foodservice and hospitality sectors, providing companies an excellent platform to discover new trends, expand their business and reach the right buyers. The third edition of the shows will be held from 17 – 19 July 2019 at Suntec Singapore and will feature an expanded programme line-up including fringe events, competitions, as well as a more diverse range of chefs, bartenders and speciality food and drink products and technologies. SFFA and RPB Asia will also see the launch of the new Industry Ambassadors programme, harnessing the power of industry insights to ensure that the needs of suppliers and buyers are fully catered to. Thks to @themangoagency for the invite!
.
.
.
.
.

DONT FORGET TO FOLLOW @plazaagora FOR MORE UPDATES ON WHAT’S IN STORE. LESS THAN 2 DAYS AWAY!
-
A party without a cake is just a meeting. And what’s this year’s Summit without some shopping and dining?
-
For the first time ever, Safinah will be having its very own own dedicated merchants’ area, half of the hall at Suntec will be dedicated to retail therapy; with food stalls and a flea market that’s open to the general public. Shop, dine and come over for a talk or two at the Summit!
-
Introducing: PLAZA AGORA
-
Agora is Greek for a place of gathering. Hence at Plaza Agora, you’ll be gathered with the best of the best, all under one roof!
-
The Plaza will feature:-
1. Tingi Point (Tagalog for Retail) - where you shop for clothes and food 
2. Suuqa Suuqa Square (Somali for Gathering) - where the kids play and have fun
3. Mangan Corner (Javanese for Eat) - where you dine and refuel yourself
-
Again, it’s open to public so come on down and see what we have in store. Check out @plazaagora as we’ll be updating more booths available on the big day!
-
LOCK IN THE DATES! Bring the whole family down to this year’s Spiritual Summit and Plaza Agora. Special offers available for those who register in groups of 10 and above! DM us if you have any queries or register now for summit at tinyurl.com/SSummit2019

text:
[ SingPost AGM ] Increase in (lower-margin) eCommerce-related volumes of larger items such as ~2kg parcels coming through the postal system experienced growth from China, albeit its recent slowdown due to US-China trade war, has offset the decrease in (higher-margin) traditional mail volumes such as domestic letter mail volumes. In addition, under outsourced management by CapitaLand Mall Asia, SingPost Centre retail mall achieved 98.9% committed occupancy, and profit on operating activities for its Property segment grew 29.8%.
.
However, Post and Parcel segment’s domestic letter mail volumes are generally in a structural decline due to paperless substitution, and its ~45% market-share in the last-mile delivery network game in Singapore faces fierce & fragmented competition (e.g. DHL, FedEx, UPS, Q-Express, Ninja Van). Moreover, SingPost may needs to address the ‘grave concerns’ raised by IMDA over recent service lapses and invest more in postal infrastructure before the regulator may allow postage rate increase (since 2014). In addition, higher performance-based compensation for key management did not really help to turnaround Trade Global and Jagged Peak in US which lead to their total impairment of S$98.7million and widened operating loss in the eCommerce segment of S$51.9million. Furthermore, SingPost’s diluted stake in its Financial assets designated as FVTOCI, Shenzhen 4PX Information and Technology, continued to face losses mainly due to set-up cost from further investment into logistics park by Alibaba’s Cainiao. Moreover, GD Express Warrants had swung from a S$1.84million fair value gain in 2018 to a S$15.5million fair value loss in 2019.
.
The Group’s dividend policy is based on a dividend payout ratio ranging from 60% to 80% of underlying net profit for each FY. Over past 5 years, dividends have decreased from S$0.0625/share to S$0.0350/share, as that is not at fundamentally sustainable level.
.
With Group CEO Mr Paul Coutts.

A party without a cake is just a meeting. And what’s this year’s Summit without some shopping and dining?

-
Agora is Greek for a place of gathering. Hence at Plaza Agora, you’ll be gathered with the best of the best, all under one roof!

The Plaza will feature:-

2. Suuqa Suuqa Square (Somali for Gathering) - where the kids play and have fun

text:
Last night's HIIT bootcamp session with @psgkalasagmountaineers and Myanmar Dragon boat team.
.
.
1st round WO/ Cardio using #marbarzapp, 2 loops of the running track (800m)with drills in between. Slow jog, sprints, walking lunges, and bear walk.
.
.
2nd round Core WO
1min workout /
20secs rest bet drills /
2mins rest between sets /
2 sets 
1. Push ups by command
2. Visit ups
3. Bicycle crunch
4. Commandos 
5. Side crunches
6. Leg press ups
7. Superman
.
.
 Every week, we are changing our program to make it more fun and interesting. It's hard yeah, but you'll be surprised you managed to complete all drills. Invite your friends and Join us next time: @archkrishna
.

text:
Paris Baguette - NOT French as the name suggests, and apparently a huge worldwide chain that originated from Korea. Go figure.🤔 Their salad was pretty decent and tasty - a choice of 1 base and 3 salad “toppings”. The salmon and avocado sandwich though.... pretty darn basic. And the bread 🥖... definitely NOT French and definitely NOT a baguette. 🤷🏻‍♀️

text:
A couple of years ago If someone would have told me that I would be living from a backpack and traveling to a different country every month, then I would probably told them to stop taking drugs 🤯 but here I am and I love it so much 😊⁣
⁣
Sometimes it’s hard to try something new because of our fears (mine were that people won’t speak my language, I don’t speak good enough English, what if something happens to me, etc). This is natural but you also have to ask yourself what if it will be the most incredible experience of your life? Jump in and don’t let the doubts to stop you. 🤸🏼‍♀️ ⁣
⁣
🇨🇿⁣
⁣
Kdyby mi pár let zpátky někdo řekl, že budu žít jenom s batohem na zádech a každý měsíc být v jiné zemi. Nejspíše bych mu řekla, ať přestane brát ty drogy. Že mu to nesvědčí.🤯 A hle tady jsem a neskutečně mi to baví.😊⁣ ⁣

Vím že někdy je to složité zkusit něco nového a často nám v tom brání strach ( že nebudou mluvit anglicky a nebo že já nemluvím dostatečně jazyk, co když se mi něco stane atd.) To je běžné. Ale musíte se zeptat sami sebe. Co když to může být ten nejkrásnější zážitek v mém životě ? Neváhejte a udělejte ten krok v před 🤸🏼‍♂️

That said, power and greatness should not be confused. Sometimes, they do overlap. 
Do they overlap all the time? Certainly not. When they do coincide, we are probably dealing with a true leader. When they do not , we may be in business with a fake one.

text:
Many ladies spend money and time to put on fake lashes to look pretty or they went for lash growth treatment in salon . This is a huge market . 
Imagine my surprise when I tried the cheap and easy DIY version and my poor lashes started getting thicker 🙌🏻 This works because Cedarwood and Lavender both support healthy hair growth, help keep the lashes clean and can also prolong the life of your mascara.

To use oils in your mascara you don’t need many at all, I use one drop each and mix the mascara super well. It’s such a small amount that no irritation occurs so make sure you don’t use too much when you mix it up. It’s also better to do this with a new tube of mascara.

Abang: Eh sekejap, diorang pon atleast pakai 2pcs each ae, hmmm. So takpe I order total 8pcs, for the 4 of us.

Me: Okay abang, why not u teros amik 10pcs. And i will top up another 2 pcs for FREE. So total u ada 12pcs. The extra 4pcs, u boleh hadiah kan to ur parents. And on top of that, i will provide FREE delivery, sampai depan rumah.

Abang: serious? Eh ok la kalau macam tu, why didnt u tell me earlier?? 😁

So guys, current promotion....
